05646nam a22007335i 9780823295128DE-B159720230103011142.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||230103t20221998nyu    fo  d z      eng d  a97808232951287 a10.1515/97808232951282doi  a(DE-B1597)626426  a(OCoLC)1322124654  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  anyucUS-NY 7aPHI0220002bisacsh1 aSimon, Anthony O., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aAcquaintance With the Absolute :bThe Philosophical Achievement of Yves R. Simon /cAnthony O. Simon. 1aNew York, NY : bFordham University Press, c[2022] 4c©1998  a1 online resource (329 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tCONTENTS -- tEDITOR'S NOTE -- tACKNOWLEDGMENTS -- tA BRIEF CHRONOLOGY -- tIntroduction: Immanent in the Souls of Men -- tPart I ESSAYS -- t1 Yves R. Simon's Metaphysics of Action -- t2 Yves R. Simon's Philosophy of Science -- t3 Yves R. Simon and the Neo- Tho mist Tradition in Epistemology -- t4 Yves R. Simon on Law, Nature, and Practical Reason -- t5 Yves R. Simon on Liberty and Authority -- t6 Practical Wisdom in the Thought of Yves R. Simon -- tPart II Bibliography -- tYves R. Simon: A Definitive Bibliography, 1923-1996 -- tIndexes -- tNotes on the Contributors0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aAcquaintance with the Absolute is the first collected volume of essays devoted to the thought of Yves r. Simon, a thinker widely regarded as one of the great teachers and philosophers of our time. Each piece in this collection of essays thoughtfully complements the others to offer a qualifiedly panoramic look at the work and thought of philosopher Yves R. Simon. The six essays presented not only treat some major areas of Simon’s thought, pointing out their lucidity and originality, but also his underpinning metaphysics, so central to his thought. Rather than attempt to present all aspects of this patient, careful, and penetrating thinker, these essays select enough to situate Simon’s philosophical excavations – especially his moral, political and action theory – among contemporary Thomistic philosophy. In defending philosophy as a valid way of knowing, Simon gives us an approach we can use to avoid contemporary dilemmas in the philosophy of science. Simon holds that philosophical truths both justify scientific method as a way of knowing the real and provide a basis for distinguishing what is ontologically significant in a scientific theory from what is not. This view allows us to avoid the apparently irrational conclusions of quantum mechanics without reducing scientific theories to being mere projections of our conceptual systems. Though aspects of some of the essays are suited for students of Simon’s thought, the essays as a whole introduce the less familiar reader to this great thinking and, further, invite him or her to pursue Simon’s own texts. The volume is enhanced by the inclusion of a definitive Yves R. Simon bibliography 1923-1996. The annotated bibliography is cross-reference in detail, revealing the astonishing variety of topics Simon treated.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 03. Jan 2023) 7aPHILOSOPHY / Religious.2bisacsh1 aBittinger, Russell, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDennehy, Raymond L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKnasas, John F. X, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKuic, Vukan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMulvaney, Robert J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNelson, Ralph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchall, James V., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/voc